This is a Yugoslavian M-57 / M57 Tokarev in 7.62x25mm.  The firearm is manufactured at the Zastava factory and imported by PW Arms of Redmond, Virginia.  It has the Yugoslavian crest on top of the slide.  

I have fired the weapon many times and found it to be a reliable, fire breathing, bullet launching, ammo chewing machine.  The recoil and firepower is somewhere between a .22LR and a Howitzer… But it’s closer to the Howitzer.  

I have cleaned the firearm after every range trip.  As the picture shows, I fire name brand factory loads through it.  The bore is clean and the grooves deep and prominent.  

The firearm comes with 3 magazines, the issued holster, the issued cleaning rod, and 2,350-rounds (forty-four 50-packs and three 60-packs).  The images should nicely represent what comes with the pistol.  If you could take a moment to appreciate the picture with the shiny bore I’d appreciate it – it turns out it’s hard to take a picture of a bore with a cell phone camera.  

This is the Mail Carrier of pistols – it’ll work in the rain, sleet, and snow.  If you are looking for a sidearm with stopping power and durability consider this as a suitable choice. This is a Yugoslavian M-57 / M57 Tokarev in 7.62x25mm.  The firearm is manufactured at the Zastava factory and imported by PW Arms of Redmond, Virginia.  It has the Yugoslavian crest on top of the slide.  

I have fired the weapon many times and found it to be a reliable, fire breathing, bullet launching, ammo chewing machine.  The recoil and firepower is somewhere between a .22LR and a Howitzer… But it’s closer to the Howitzer.  

I have cleaned the firearm after every range trip.  As the picture shows, I fire name brand factory loads through it.  The bore is clean and the grooves deep and prominent.  

The firearm comes with 3 magazines, the issued holster, the issued cleaning rod, and 2,380-rounds (forty-four 50-packs and three 60-packs).  The images should nicely represent what comes with the pistol.  If you could take a moment to appreciate the picture with the shiny bore I’d appreciate it – it turns out it’s hard to take a picture of a bore with a cell phone camera.  

This is the Mail Carrier of pistols – it’ll work in the rain, sleet, and snow.  If you are looking for a sidearm with stopping power and durability consider this as a suitable choice.  It’s solid enough that if you manage to miss your target with all 2,380-rounds you can still flip it over and beat them with the thing.  

See the picture, think happy thoughts, don’t tell your wife, and contact me with an offer.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Phoenix Arms HP22 w/ holster and 22lr ammo
postcontent:
I'm selling my Phoenix Arms HP22 pistol.  It comes with one 10-round magazine and a leather IWB clip-on holster.  It also includes over 350 rounds of 22 long rifle ammunition (40 rounds CCI Blazer, approximately 20 rounds of Remington lead round-point, and the rest Federal 36 grain copper-plated hollow point).

I am the original owner, but I don't have the owner's manual or anything anymore.  The gun is in good shape, with some minor holster wear and a little bit of build-up (oxidation perhaps?) on the back strap and bottom of the magazine.  It can be scrubbed off, I just scraped a little off with my thumbnail, but it is a cosmetic flaw.  I have fired under 500 rounds through this pistol with no problem, except the last time I went to the range I had a couple failures to feed.  This may just mean the magazine's ready for a good cleaning or needs a new spring, but I have another 22 pistol and my wife's starting to complain about too many guns.  This is a good, solid metal gun that has been reliable for over a decade, while small enough to slip into a pocket or keep in small, inconspicuous pop-out tray in your truck or van.  It's also a single-stack gun, which mean's the grip is narrow enough for people with small hands to get their fingers around, and is ideal for training new shooters with.

I'm not looking to make a huge profit off this gun, but I am looking to get a fair value, especially with the ammo that's getting more expensive and almost impossible to find these days.  Shoot me an offer, whether cash or trade, and we'll talk.  I'm willing to add cash and more ammo for the right deal.  First one with cash (or trade) that meets me gets this – I'm not going to hold it for your paycheck in a month.  Face to face transaction preferred, although I'm willing to ship to an FFL at your expense.  CCW preferred, though not required.  

***NOTE:  Due to the overwhelming response in the first 24 hours, I will not accept any offers less than $200 now.  Write me all the hate mail you want, but I've had too many offers for just the ammo to think this package is worth less than this.  And no, I will not split it up.
